ranked_diseases.explanation: Strong match with full cheeks, developmental delays (speech/motor), feeding difficulties, synophrys, and characteristic facial features including depressed nasal bridge and anteverted nares.
Fits well with synophrys, developmental delays, feeding difficulties, and facial dysmorphisms. Strabismus and anxiety are also common features.
Consistent with severe speech delay, motor delay, drooling, feeding difficulties, strabismus, and anxiety. Full cheeks and happy demeanor are typical.
Matches with square face, full cheeks, developmental delays, and behavioral issues (anxiety). Deep-set eyes and depressed nasal bridge are supportive features.
Presents with intellectual disability, speech delay, and characteristic facial features including synophrys and anteverted nares. Behavioral issues are common.
Could explain multiple features including feeding difficulties, developmental delays, and ocular abnormalities (strabismus, hypermetropia), though missing key diagnostic criteria.
Characterized by speech delay, characteristic facial features, and developmental delays. The deeply set eyes and feeding difficulties in infancy are supportive.
